					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/wishun" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1204404); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1204404&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610183403" alt="wishun" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1204404)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/wishun" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1204404); return false;" >wishun</a></span> <span class="odate time_1381341427 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">09 Oct 2013 17:57</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1867308">
									

<p>I like that, 1678 certainly matches the tone and atmosphere very well. Hmmm&#8230;let's see&#8230;<br />
Might be that some of the cultists managed to survive and learn to avoid the worm-maddened mechanical monstrosities. With time, they even managed to tame a portion of the prison-device into a rough reflection of their nearly-forgotten home. For a while, they thrived in the security of their constructed pseudo-London, trusting in the wind-up &quot;bobbies&quot; to keep them safe.</p>
<p>But the corruption of the Worm is insidious and implacable. The beginning of the end was a single small &quot;bird&quot;, a sparrow with wings of rusted iron. In contrast to the silently vigilant camera-pigeons the sparrow's gears clashed and ground against each other. Its song was the scream of tortured metal. One bird was soon two, then a flock, until the streetlights were hidden behind the blur of their flitting casings and the pattern of their screams drilled away at even the stoutest sanity.</p>
<p>The city council only realized the true depth of the threat when it was too late. As psychosis spread like gangrene, they activated The Project. The Project was the center of all unLondon science and industry, an attempt to invert the device that brought the First Fathers to limbo. It was far from ready. But the council, feeling the beginnings of the Pattern Screamer madness themselves, flipped the switch anyway. And it worked! &#8230;after a fashion. The Project brought unLondon out of Limbo and safely back into the real world; it just didn't bring the residents along. Back in Limbo, the suddenly refuge-less citizens of unLondon are now nothing but grisly lubricant in the gears of the Worm's abandoned minions.</p>

							</div>

								
					
